cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.AI, cs.AR, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper proposes a novel neuro-fuzzy system that is based on the creation of fuzzy relations using a new implication method. This suggests that the paper is related to neural computing and learning. 
2. cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) - The paper proposes a hardware implementation of the neuro-fuzzy system using memristor crossbar-based analog circuits. This suggests that the paper is related to emerging technologies in hardware design. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a computing system that can be used for creating artificial brain. This suggests that the paper is related to artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper proposes a hardware implementation of the neuro-fuzzy system using analog circuits. This suggests that the paper is related to hardware architecture. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a fault-tolerant and hierarchically expandable computing system that can compute operations in real time. This suggests that the paper is related to systems and control.
